 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'Calinou', 'comment_id': 526843524.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-31 16:18:56+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "I don't think we plan on using GitHub Pages for hosting, so we could go for Hugo and deploy the HTML ourselves on TuxFamily. I'd favor Hugo over Jekyll for two reasons:

