 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'jcs224', 'comment_id': 663342112.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-24 04:32:30+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_4', 'text': "@username_0 @username_1 @username_2 Bumping this as I just ran into a problem with trying to run the OctoberCMS site on Windows. Looks like the workflow for working on the site in a local dev environment favors a UNIX environment (.sh scripts and whatnot). While I could (and probably will) work out the issue, I would prefer separating the _website_ from the _content_. Static sites make this very easy. 

